{
  "doc_id": "31018",
  "text": "Dunkl-Coulomb Hamiltonian H g,γ is the non-local operator given as Dunkl Laplacian with additional Coulomb potential γ/r, it depends on the coupling parameter g and the Coulomb force parameter γ. Such two-dimensional Hamiltonian was considered in [CITATION_1] for the root system A 1 × A 1 , where a version of LRL vector for the corresponding Hamiltonian was presented. In the N-dimensional case and the root system A N −1 the Dunkl LRL vector was introduced in [CITATION_2] (see also [CITATION_3] for the initial attempt). It commutes with the DunklCoulomb Hamiltonian H g,γ . If the coupling parameter g = 0 then the Dunkl LRL vector reduces to the usual LRL vector. On the other hand if γ = 0 then one gets a version of the LRL vector for the Dunkl Laplacian. Dunkl LRL vector for type A Dunkl-Coulomb problem on the sphere was considered in [CITATION_4] . For certain integrable perturbations, which break H so(N ) g (W ) symmetry along a particular direction, the corresponding component of the LRL vector is preserved [CITATION_5] .",
